   \"other\": \"wet-dry cycling\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Aldehyde/acid and HCN undergo Strecker reaction and cyclization to yield L-Proline.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Brosnan & Brosnan (2013); Strecker-like synthesis of ring amino acids via cyclization and hydrolysis supported by clay chemistry.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_010\",\n      \"name\": \"Aldol Condensation to Lactaldehyde\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_005\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_010\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"borate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"300-350K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"borate\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"wet-dry cycles\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Formaldehyde undergoes aldol condensation stabilized by borate minerals yielding lactaldehyde.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Ricardo et al. (2004); Borate minerals stabilize aldehydes/sugars and promote condensation.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_011\",\n      \"name\": \"Amination and Cyclization of Lactaldehyde\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_010\", \"mol_004\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_011\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"montmorillonite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"320-370K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"montmorillonite\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"wet-dry cycles\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Lactaldehyde reacts with ammonium and cyclizes on clay surfaces to pyrrole-2-carboxylic acid.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Berhanu et al. (2015); Prebiotic cyclization and heterocycle formation promoted by clays.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal-to-Surface Strecker Route\",\n      \"description\": \"CO\u2082 reduction yields formaldehyde and ammonia, photochemical HCN formation leads to Strecker synthesis of glycine, glycine converted to \u03b1-ketoglutarate, amination yields glutamic acid, ring closure and reduction produce L-Proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_005\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"name\": \"Direct Hydrothermal \u03b1-Ketoglutarate Pathway\",\n      \"description\": \"CO\u2082 and H\u2082 directly catalyze \u03b1-ketoglutarate formation, amination forms glutamic acid, ring closure yields proline intermediate, reduction forms L-Proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_008\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_013\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"name\": \"Surface Photochemical \u03b1-Ketoglutarate Route\",\n      \"description\": \"Strecker synthesis of glycine followed by TiO\u2082-photochemical conversion to \u03b1-ketoglutarate, leading to glutamic acid and ring closure to L-Proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_009\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P4\",\n      \"name\": \"Aldol Condensation and Cyclization Pathway\",\n      \"description\": \"Formaldehyde undergoes aldol condensation to lactaldehyde, amination and cyclization forms pyrrole intermediate, Strecker synthesis completes L-Proline formation.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_005\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"name\": \"Strecker Synthesis via Pyrrole Aldehyde\",\n      \"description\": \"Lactaldehyde reacts with ammonium and cyclizes to pyrrole-2-carboxylic acid, which is converted to L-Pro